</para><quote depth="1"><quotepara depth="1"> Do you generally put everything in your model into groups?
</quotepara></quote><para depth="0">
Not necessarily everything, Kenny, but certainly everything I plan to
put on a layer other than 0.

</para><para depth="0">There are, of course, other reasons to group things (and sometimes
it's better to use components instead of groups), but if you're going
to put something on a layer so you can toggle its visibility, you must
group or componentize it first, leaving the individual edges and faces
on Layer0. When you turn off a Layer to hide objects (groups and
components) on that layer, the individual entities are also hidden,
even though they are not on that layer.

</para><para depth="0">-Gully

